{{Top|leg|canon=Rafa life crystal}}
'''Life crystals''', found in the system of [[Rafa IV|Rafa]], were a mysterious type of crystal that many claimed were good for the body when kept in close proximity. The crystals were harvested from trees that only grew in [[Life-orchard]]s<ref name="TEGtPaM">''[[The Essential Guide to Planets and Moons]]''</ref> which could only be harvested by manual labor which was reserved for the local less intelligent humanoids and criminals from out of system. In actuality, the trees were a device used to sap the intelligence of the general population, a safety precaution to prevent the conquest of the Sharu civilization.

This effect drained the intelligence of the mythical [[Sharu/Legends|Sharu]], turning them into the [[Sharu/Legends|Toka]]. When [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] and [[Vuffi Raa]] discovered the [[Mindharp of Sharu/Legends|Mindharp]] of Sharu, the intelligence of the Toka was restored, turning them back into the Sharu. This action also destroyed the Life Gardens, effectively putting an end to the production of life-crystals.

Before the fall of the Republic, life crystals sold for around five thousand [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]], but after the Republic fell, life crystals were only available on the black market at exorbitant prices.<ref name="A Campaign Guide to the Centrality">{{GamerCite|5|A Campaign Guide to the Centrality}}</ref>

